    {
      "id": "18a17ef2ec7ec53c674086a26b6f2d891aa2e83a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2023-09-20 04:29:12.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nTBF, it looks like updake of complicated commit hooks is low so the most impact is by running things server-side.\n\nNot to discourage you from working on this of course, jsut to be realistic.\n\nAlso if you have cool ideas about what extra stuff janitor could be handling better or checkign extra, feel free to contribute. (sorry the code is a mess, it's written in python by a C programmer (me))",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "c7feb3c928c07c0ed10d4ed493b3f00a119e2ede",
