      "date": "2023-09-20 04:32:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nBuild 98662 (patch #1) will not be tested because: it is marked forbuildonly",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "8e9caece3789145c070bba0cef7ff385c2fb5260",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 931,
        "name": "Timothy Day",
        "email": "timday@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "timday"
      },
      "date": "2023-09-20 15:27:38.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI tend to assume I'm the primary (or only) user of some of tools I've written and upstreamed. But I hope it helps out some similarly minded people in the future. I think a python version of this hook might make it easier to add some features that Andreas was interested in.\n\nOne Gerrit Janitor feature I was interested in was adding a `Test-Parameters` setting to force the Janitor to run. I looked through the code a while back, but never got around to writing a patch. If I do that, should I just open a PR against https://github.com/verygreen/lustretester/tree/master?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "cbd072727b28619bd623b036fb1f3759178a370e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2023-09-20 15:43:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nUnfortunately, rewriting prepare-commit-msg in Python would reduce my ability to contribute to it, but I'm sure the experience will be good for me.\n\nNote also that there are some test cases in the contrib/git-hooks/tests directory, but I think they are mostly for the \"commit-msg\" hook and not \"prepare-commit-msg\".",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
